# Day 06 - ARP Analysis

## Topic
Address Resolution Protocol (ARP)

## What I Learned
- ARP stands for Address Resolution Protocol.
- ARP maps an IP address to a MAC address.
- ARP Request asks: "Who has this IP address?"
- ARP Reply answers with the device's MAC address.
- Every device on a local network has a unique MAC address.

## Tools Used
- Kali Linux
- Wireshark

## Key Observation
I captured ARP Request and ARP Reply packets in Wireshark and observed how devices discover each other's MAC addresses on the local network.
